  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agro-Passport / Farmforce</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Funding has been received for the Agro-Passport program, which will introduce, showcase, test, and scale Farmforce, a proven digital, commercial traceability and supply chain management system to Latin America, in partnership with Mercy Corps. The Farmforce platform is an initiative of the Syngenta Foundation for Sustainable Agriculture (SFSA), which aims to create value for resource-poor small farmers in developing countries through innovation in sustainable agriculture and the activation of value chains.  SFSA has developed and tested Farmforce in Kenya, Burkina Faso, Nigeria, Ghana and Zimbabwe, and believes that they are ready to expand to new geographies in Latin America.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Program is focused on using Farmforce to:

1) Increase the capacity of exporters to manage more farmers which will increase their ability to access higher-value markets
2) Improve the ability to analyze and track data to enable targeted training for production improvements, identify inappropriate pesticides that could cause produce to be rejected, and identify strategies to reduce losses.</narrative>
  </description>
